  "texts": [
    "To verify the reliability of the ITR values, each functionalization variant was simulated at least three times with independently generated functional group distribution and initial atomic velocities.",
    "The resulting thermal resistance values were found to be consistent across repetitions, confirming the reproducibility of the results.",
    "In addition, convergence tests were carried out (see SM, Figure S1) and confirmed the temporal stability of both the temperature profiles and the corresponding ITR values.",
    "Given the total amount of energy 〈𝐸〉 passing through area 𝐴 in time 𝑡, the heat flux was defined as:",
    "In addition to the heat flux calculation method described above, we also employed an alternative approach that enables the decomposition of heat flux based on the generalized Irving-Kirkwood formalism 96, which enables decomposition of the heat flux into contributions from different atom groups."
  ]
}